     --property

         Optional attribute name/value pairs for configuring  the
         JavaMail resource. Enterprise Server-specific mail- pre-
         fix is converted to standard mail prefix.  The  JavaMail
         API documentation lists the properties you might want to
         set.

OPERANDS
     jndi-name
         The JNDI name of the JavaMail resource to be created. It
         is  a  recommended practice to use the naming subcontext
         prefix mail/ for JavaMail resources.

EXAMPLES
     Example 1 Creating a JavaMail Resource

     This   example   creates   a   JavaMail    resource    named
     mail/MyMailSession.  The  JNDI  name  for a JavaMail session
     resource customarily includes the mail/ naming subcontext.

       asadmin> create-javamail-resource --mailhost localhost
       --mailuser sample --fromaddress sample@sun.com mail/MyMailSession
